name: Laura Kelly
tweet: This week during a stop in Hutchinson on my Kansan to Kansan Budget Listening Tour, a Lincoln Elementary 6th-grader told me his family can't afford their prescriptions without insurance. Even the youngest Kansans get it — it's our duty to expand Medicaid.  https://t.co/VW3i2gM4tF

name: Laura Kelly
tweet: But we still have work to do. I promise I will continue working for Kansas families every day. We will keep our state on the path forward. (3/3)

name: Laura Kelly
tweet: We've accomplished a lot. We balanced our state's budget without a tax increase, funded our schools & are rebuilding our state agencies. We reinstated protections to our LGBTQ+ state employees and established the Office of Rural Prosperity. And much more. (2/3)

name: Laura Kelly
tweet: One year ago today, the people of Kansas elected me to be their Governor. Kansans wanted me to rebuild our state and get us back on track. And I take this responsibility seriously. name: Laura Kelly
